external_knowledge:
Popular tweets: tweets with engagement_score > 100; 
Emotional tone: average sentiment score; 
Most discussed geopolitical entities: geopolitical entities with more than 5 associated tweets.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS high_engagement_tweets
FROM engagements
WHERE engagement_score > 1000;

SELECT COUNT(tweet_id) AS tweet_count
FROM tweet_sources
WHERE source_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(engagement_score) AS average_engagement_score
FROM engagements
WHERE tweet_id = '0';

SELECT engagement_score
FROM engagements
WHERE tweet_id = '1';

external_knowledge:
- Mentions refer to the number of unique tweets; 
- Online discussions refer to tweets on social media platforms; 
- Sentiment scores measure the emotional tone of the tweets, ranging from negative to positive; 
- Engagement scores measure how much users interact with tweets through likes, retweets, replies, and quotes.
